70 int ML_Gen_MGHierarchy_UsingAggregation(ML *ml, int start,
71  int increment_or_decrement, ML_Aggregate *ag)
72 {
73  int level, idata, i;
74  double dnnz = 0;
75  ML_Aggregate *ml_ag;
76 #ifdef ML_TIMING
77  double t0;
78 #endif
79 
80  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 8 < ML_Get_PrintLevel())
81  {
82  printf("Entering ML_Gen_MGHierarchy_UsingAggregation\n");
83  fflush(stdout);
84  }
85  ML_memory_check("L%d:gen_hier start",start);
86 
87  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
88  /* if user does not provide a ML_Aggregate object, create a default */
89  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
90 
91  if ( ag == NULL ) ML_Aggregate_Create( &ml_ag );
92  else ml_ag=ag;
93  ML_Aggregate_Set_MaxLevels( ml_ag, ml->ML_num_levels);
94  ML_Aggregate_Set_StartLevel( ml_ag, start );
95 
96  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
97  /* create multilevel hierarchy */
98  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
99 
100  idata = 0;
101  idata = ML_gmax_int(idata, ml->comm);
102  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ml_ag->print_flag < ML_Get_PrintLevel())
103  ML_Aggregate_Print( ml_ag );
104 #ifdef ML_TIMING
105  t0 = GetClock();
106 #endif
107  idata = ML_gmax_int(idata, ml->comm);
108 
109  if (increment_or_decrement == ML_INCREASING)
110  {
111  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
112  /* coarse scheme == 4 ==> domain decomposition */
113  /* -------------------------------------------------------------- */
114  if ( ml_ag->coarsen_scheme == 4 )
115  {
116  level = ML_Gen_MGHierarchy(ml, start, ML_AGG_Increment_Two_Level,
117  ML_AGG_Gen_DDProlongator, NULL, ml_ag);
118  }
119  else
120  {
121  level = ML_Gen_MGHierarchy(ml, start, ML_AGG_Increment_Level,
122  ML_AGG_Gen_Prolongator, NULL, ml_ag);
123  }
124  }
125  else if (increment_or_decrement == ML_DECREASING)
126  {
127  if ( ml_ag->coarsen_scheme == 4 )
128  {
129  level = ML_Gen_MGHierarchy(ml, start, ML_AGG_Decrement_Two_Level,
130  ML_AGG_Gen_DDProlongator, NULL, ml_ag);
131  }
132  else
133  {
134  level = ML_Gen_MGHierarchy(ml, start, ML_AGG_Decrement_Level,
135  ML_AGG_Gen_Prolongator, NULL, ml_ag);
136  }
137  }
138  else
139  {
140  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 )
141  {
142  printf("ML_Gen_MGHierarchy_UsingAggregation : Unknown ");
143  printf("increment_or_decrement choice\n");
144  }
145  exit(1);
146  }
147 #ifdef ML_TIMING
148  t0 = GetClock() - t0;
149  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 9 )
150  printf("Aggregation total setup time = %e seconds\n", t0);
151 #endif
152 
153  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
154  /* compute operator complexity */
155  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
156 
157  if (increment_or_decrement == ML_INCREASING)
158  dnnz = ml->Amat[level-start-1].N_nonzeros;
159  else if (increment_or_decrement == ML_DECREASING)
160  dnnz = ml->Amat[start+1-level].N_nonzeros;
161  dnnz = ML_gsum_double( dnnz, ml->comm );
162  ml_ag->operator_complexity += dnnz;
163 
164  if (ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 10) {
165  for (i=0; i<level; i++) {
166  int thisLevel = ml->LevelID[i];
167  ML_Operator_Profile(ml->Amat+thisLevel,NULL);
168  if (i != level-1) ML_Operator_Profile(ml->Rmat+thisLevel,NULL);
169  if (i != 0) ML_Operator_Profile(ml->Pmat+thisLevel,NULL);
170  }
171  }
172 
173  idata = ML_gmax_int(idata, ml->comm);
174  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ml_ag->print_flag < ML_Get_PrintLevel())
175  ML_Aggregate_Print_Complexity( ml_ag );
176  idata = ML_gmax_int(idata, ml->comm);
177 
178  if ( ag == NULL ) ML_Aggregate_Destroy( &ml_ag );
179  ML_memory_check("gen hierarchy end");
180 
181  return(level);
182 }

184 /* ************************************************************************* */
185 /* generate multilevel hierarchy given a subroutine for generating */
186 /* prolongation operators (version 2 : with ML_Aggregate given) */
187 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
188 
189 int ML_Gen_MGHierarchy(ML *ml, int fine_level,
190  int (*next_level)(ML *, int, void *),
191  int (*user_gen_prolongator)(ML *, int, int, void *),
192  void *data, ML_Aggregate *ag)
193 {
194  int level, next, flag, count=1;
195  int i, j, k, bail_flag, N_input_vector;
196  ML_Operator *Pmat;
197  ML_CommInfoOP *getrow_comm;
198  ML_Operator *Ptent;
199  ML_Aggregate_Viz_Stats *grid_info;
200 #ifdef ML_TIMING
201  double t0;
202 #endif
203 
204  if (ag->nullspace_corrupted == ML_YES) {
205  printf("Can not reuse aggregate object when the fine grid operator\n");
206  printf("has a nontrivial null space. It is possible to keep \n");
207  printf("tentative prolongator within smoothed aggregation by\n");
208  printf("invoking ML_Aggregate_Set_Reuse(...) before hierarchy\n");
209  printf("generation and then on subsequent hierarchy generations use\n");
210  printf("ML_Gen_MGHierarchy_UsingSmoothedAggr_ReuseExistingAgg().\n");
211 
212  exit(-1);
213  }
214 
215  ml->ML_finest_level = fine_level;
216  level = fine_level;
217  next = next_level(ml, level, ag);
218  k = 0;
219  ml->LevelID[k++] = fine_level;
220 
221  while (next >= 0)
222  {
223 
224  /* This if-else supports an ALEGRA capability. */
225  if (data == NULL)
226  flag = (*user_gen_prolongator)(ml, level, next,(void *)ag);
227  else
228  flag = (*user_gen_prolongator)(ml, level, next,(void *)data);
229 
230  if (flag < 0) break;
231  ML_memory_check("L%d: prolongator end",level);
232 
233  /* Now check to make sure prolongator has zero columns. */
234  Pmat = ml->Pmat+next;
235  bail_flag = 0;
236  N_input_vector = Pmat->invec_leng;
237  getrow_comm = Pmat->getrow->pre_comm;
238  if ( getrow_comm != NULL)
239  {
240  for (i = 0; i < getrow_comm->N_neighbors; i++) {
241  for (j = 0; j < getrow_comm->neighbors[i].N_send; j++) {
242  if (getrow_comm->neighbors[i].send_list[j] >= N_input_vector) {
243  bail_flag = 1;
244  }
245  }
246  }
247  }
248  /* If check has failed on any processor, clean up current level & break
249  from main loop. */
250  ML_gsum_scalar_int(&bail_flag,&j,ml->comm);
251  if (bail_flag)
252  {
253  if (Pmat->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 5 < ML_Get_PrintLevel()) {
254  printf("(%d) In ML_Gen_MGHierarchy: Bailing from AMG hierarchy build on level %d, where fine level = %d ........\n",
255  Pmat->comm->ML_mypid,level,fine_level);
256  fflush(stdout);
257  }
258  if (ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 5 < ML_Get_PrintLevel()) {
259  printf("(%d) In ML_Gen_MGHierarchy: Nlevels = %d fine_level = %d coarsest_level = %d\n",
260  ml->comm->ML_mypid,fine_level-count+1,fine_level,count);
261  fflush(stdout);
262  }
263  break; /* from main loop */
264 
265  }
266  /* end of check */
267  ML_Gen_Restrictor_TransP(ml, level, next, NULL);
268  ML_Operator_ChangeToSinglePrecision(&(ml->Pmat[next]));
269  ML_memory_check("L%d: TransP end",level);
270 
271 #ifdef ML_TIMING
272  t0 = GetClock();
273 #endif
274  ML_Gen_AmatrixRAP(ml, level, next);
275  ML_memory_check("L%d: RAP end",level);
276 
277  /* project the coordinates (if any) to the next coarser level */
278  if (ag->P_tentative != NULL)
279  Ptent = ag->P_tentative[next];
280  else
281  Ptent = &(ml->Pmat[next]);
282 
283  grid_info =(ML_Aggregate_Viz_Stats *) ml->Amat[level].to->Grid->Grid;
284  if (grid_info) {
285  if (grid_info->x != NULL) {
286  if (ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 4 && ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0)
287  printf("ML_Gen_MGHierarchy: Projecting node coordinates from level %d to level %d\n",
288  level,next);
289  ML_Project_Coordinates(ml->Amat+level, Ptent, ml->Amat+next);
290  }
291  }
292 
293  ML_Comm_Barrier(ml->comm);
294 
295  ML_repartition_Acoarse(ml, level, next, ag, ML_TRUE, ML_FALSE);
296 
297  ML_Comm_Barrier(ml->comm);
298 
299  ML_Operator_ImplicitTranspose(&(ml->Rmat[level]),
300  &(ml->Pmat[next]), ML_TRUE);
301 
302  ML_memory_check("L%d: repartition end",level);
303 
304 #ifdef ML_TIMING
305  t0 = GetClock() - t0;
306  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 10 )
307  printf("RAP time for level %2d = %e\n", level, t0);
308 #endif
309 
310  level = next;
311  ml->LevelID[k++] = next;
312  next = next_level(ml, next, ag);
313  count++;
314  }
315  return(count);
316 }

322 int ML_AGG_Gen_Prolongator(ML *ml,int level, int clevel, void *data)
323 {
324  int Ncoarse, Nfine, gNfine, gNcoarse, ii, jj;
325  double max_eigen = -1.;
326  ML_Operator *Amat, *Pmatrix = NULL, *AGGsmoother = NULL;
327  ML_Operator **prev_P_tentatives;
328  struct ML_AGG_Matrix_Context widget;
329  ML_Krylov *kdata;
330  ML_Operator *t2 = NULL, *t3 = NULL;
331  ML_Aggregate * ag = (ML_Aggregate *) data;
332  struct MLSthing *mls_widget = NULL;
333  ML_Operator *blockMat = NULL, *Ptemp;
334  int numSmSweeps; /* polynomial degree of prolongator smoother */
335  double *dampingFactors; /* coefficients of prolongator smoother */
336  ML_Operator *tmpmat1=NULL,*tmpmat2=NULL;
337 
338  double t1=0, createPtentTime=0, smooPTime=0, eigenTime=0;
339 #ifdef ML_TIMING
340  double t0;
341  t0 = GetClock();
342 #endif
343  widget.Adiag = NULL;
344 
345  StartTimer(&t1);
346 
347  Amat = &(ml->Amat[level]);
348  numSmSweeps = ML_Aggregate_Get_DampingSweeps(ag,level);
349 
350  if (Amat->num_PDEs < ag->num_PDE_eqns) Amat->num_PDEs = ag->num_PDE_eqns;
351  if (ag->block_scaled_SA == 1) {
352  /*
353  Create block scaled and compute its eigenvalues
354  a) if the user has requested it, save this Amat into
355  the aggregate data structure.
356  */
357  mls_widget = ML_Smoother_Create_MLS();
358  ML_Gen_BlockScaledMatrix_with_Eigenvalues(Amat, -1, NULL,
359  &blockMat, mls_widget);
360  max_eigen = blockMat->lambda_max;
361  }
362  else max_eigen = Amat->lambda_max;
363 
364  widget.near_bdry = NULL;
365  Amat->num_PDEs = ag->num_PDE_eqns;
366  prev_P_tentatives = ag->P_tentative;
367 #ifdef USE_MOREACCURATE
368 if (Amat->diagonal == NULL) ML_Operator_Getrow_Diag(Amat, &(widget.Adiag));
369 else ML_DVector_GetDataPtr( Amat->diagonal, &(widget.Adiag) );
370 #endif
371 
372 
373  /*
374  widget.near_bdry = (char *) ML_allocate(sizeof(char)*Amat->outvec_leng);
375  ML_AGG_Compute_Near_Bdry(Amat, widget.near_bdry);
376  */
377 
378  Nfine = Amat->outvec_leng;
379  gNfine = ML_Comm_GsumInt( ml->comm, Nfine);
380  ML_Aggregate_Set_CurrentLevel( ag, level );
381 
382  if ( (ag->smoothP_damping_factor!=0.0) && (numSmSweeps>0) )
383  {
384  if ((ag->keep_P_tentative == ML_YES) && (prev_P_tentatives != NULL) &&
385  (prev_P_tentatives[clevel] != NULL))
386  {
387  Pmatrix = prev_P_tentatives[clevel];
388  Ncoarse = Pmatrix->invec_leng;
389  }
390  else if (ML_Aggregate_Get_Flag_SmoothExistingTentativeP(ag) == ML_YES)
391  {
392  Pmatrix = ML_Operator_halfClone( &(ml->Pmat[clevel]) );
393  /* ml->Pmat[clevel] is destroyed first. Half cloning assumes that
394  everything associated with matrix->getrow is destroyed with the
395  original operator. In this case, the getrow object should be
396  destroyed with the clone. Hence, we lie and say Pmatrix is not
397  the result of a clone....*/
398  Pmatrix->halfclone = ML_FALSE;
399 
400  Pmatrix->data_destroy = ml->Pmat[clevel].data_destroy;
401  ml->Pmat[clevel].data_destroy = NULL;
402  ml->Pmat[clevel].data = NULL;
403 
404  ML_memory_free( (void**)&(Pmatrix->matvec) );
405  Pmatrix->matvec = ml->Pmat[clevel].matvec;
406  ml->Pmat[clevel].matvec = NULL;
407 
408  if (Pmatrix->getrow != NULL) {
409  if (Pmatrix->getrow->pre_comm != NULL)
410  ML_CommInfoOP_Destroy(&(Pmatrix->getrow->pre_comm));
411  }
412  ML_memory_free( (void**)&(Pmatrix->getrow) );
413  Pmatrix->getrow = ml->Pmat[clevel].getrow;
414  ml->Pmat[clevel].getrow = NULL;
415  if (Pmatrix->label != NULL) ML_free(Pmatrix->label);
416  Pmatrix->label = ml->Pmat[clevel].label;
417  ml->Pmat[clevel].label = NULL;
418 
419  ML_Operator_Clean(&(ml->Pmat[clevel]));
420  ML_memory_alloc((void**)&(ml->Pmat[clevel].getrow),
421  sizeof(ML_GetrowFunc),"OF2");
422 
423  ml->Pmat[clevel].matvec = Pmatrix->matvec;
424  Pmatrix->matvec = NULL;
425  ml->Pmat[clevel].label = Pmatrix->label;
426  Pmatrix->label = NULL;
427  Ncoarse = Pmatrix->invec_leng;
428  }
429  else {
430  Pmatrix = ML_Operator_Create(ml->comm);
431  Ncoarse = ML_Aggregate_Coarsen(ag,Amat,&Pmatrix,ml->comm);
432  }
433  }
434  else
435  {
436  Pmatrix = &(ml->Pmat[clevel]);
437  if (Pmatrix->invec_leng == 0)
438  Ncoarse = ML_Aggregate_Coarsen(ag,Amat,&Pmatrix,ml->comm);
439  else Ncoarse = Pmatrix->invec_leng;
440  }
441  gNcoarse = ML_Comm_GsumInt( ml->comm, Ncoarse);
442 /* the next two lines added to prevent breakdown in adaptive SA */
443  gNcoarse = gNcoarse / Pmatrix->num_PDEs;
444  gNfine = gNfine / Amat->num_PDEs;
445  if ( gNcoarse == 0 || ((1.0*gNfine)/(1.0*gNcoarse+0.1) < 1.05) )
446  {
447  if (( Pmatrix != NULL ) && (ag->smoothP_damping_factor != 0.0)
448  && (numSmSweeps>0) )
449  {
450  if (ML_Aggregate_Get_Flag_SmoothExistingTentativeP(ag) == ML_YES)
451  {
452  ml->Pmat[clevel].data_destroy = Pmatrix->data_destroy;
453  Pmatrix->data_destroy = NULL;
454 
455  ML_memory_free( (void**)&(ml->Pmat[clevel].getrow) );
456  ml->Pmat[clevel].getrow = Pmatrix->getrow;
457  Pmatrix->getrow = NULL;
458 
459  ml->Pmat[clevel].data = Pmatrix->data;
460  Pmatrix->data = NULL;
461  }
462  ML_Operator_Destroy(&Pmatrix);
463  }
464  if (mls_widget != NULL) ML_Smoother_Destroy_MLS(mls_widget);
465  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 3 < ML_Get_PrintLevel()) {
466  printf("Warning: ML aborts further coarsening, perhaps diagonally dominant matrix after dropping is nearly diagonal!\n");
467  fflush(stdout);
468  }
469  return -1;
470  }
471 
472  StopTimer(&t1,&createPtentTime);
473  StartTimer(&t1);
474 
475  if ( ag->smoothP_damping_factor != 0.0 && numSmSweeps > 0 )
476  {
477  /*********************************************************
478  * If we symmetrize we need the symmetrized matrix so we
479  * don't call ML_Gimmie_Eigenvalues() here.
480  * ML_Gimmie_Eigenvalues(Amat, ML_DIAGSCALE,
481  * Amat->spectral_radius_scheme, ml->symmetrize_matrix);
482  * max_eigen = Amat->lambda_max;
483  *********************************************************/
484 
485  if (ml->symmetrize_matrix == ML_TRUE) {
486  t2 = ML_Operator_Create(Amat->comm);
487  ML_Operator_Transpose_byrow(Amat,t2);
488  t3 = ML_Operator_Create(Amat->comm);
489  ML_Operator_Add(Amat,t2,t3,ML_CSR_MATRIX,1.);
490  max_eigen = t3->lambda_max;
491  }
492 
493  if ((max_eigen < -666.) && (max_eigen > -667)) {
494  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 5)
495  printf("Calculating eigenvalue estimate using ");
496 
497  switch( Amat->spectral_radius_scheme ) {
498 
499  case ML_USE_CG: /* compute it using CG */
500  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 5)
501  printf("CG method\n");
502 
503  kdata = ML_Krylov_Create( ml->comm );
504  ML_Krylov_Set_PrintFreq( kdata, 0 );
505  ML_Krylov_Set_MaxIterations(kdata, Amat->spectral_radius_max_iters);
506  ML_Krylov_Set_ComputeEigenvalues( kdata );
507  if (ml->symmetrize_matrix ==ML_TRUE) ML_Krylov_Set_Amatrix(kdata, t3);
508  else ML_Krylov_Set_Amatrix(kdata, Amat);
509  ML_Krylov_Solve(kdata, Nfine, NULL, NULL);
510  /* This is a bit screwy in that max_eigen corresponds to Dinv A. */
511  /* This is good for Cheby smoothers but bad for smoothed agg */
512  /* if we actually filter A (significantly) as we should compute */
513  /* the eigenvalue of Dinv Afilt. */
514  max_eigen = ML_Krylov_Get_MaxEigenvalue(kdata);
515 
516  Amat->lambda_max = max_eigen;
517  Amat->lambda_min = kdata->ML_eigen_min;
518  ML_Krylov_Destroy( &kdata );
519  if ( max_eigen <= 0.0 ) {
520  printf("Gen_Prolongator warning : max eigen <= 0.0 \n");
521  max_eigen = 1.0;
522  }
523 
524  break;
525 
526  case ML_USE_ANASAZI: /* Use Anasazi */
527 #if defined(HAVE_ML_EPETRA) && defined(HAVE_ML_ANASAxI) && defined(HAVE_ML_TEUCHOS)
528  ML_Anasazi_Get_SpectralNorm_Anasazi(Amat, 0, 10, 1e-5,
529  ML_FALSE, ML_TRUE, &max_eigen);
530  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 5)
531  printf("Anasazi\n");
532 #else
533  fprintf(stderr,
534  "--enable-epetra --enable-anasazi --enable-teuchos required\n"
535  "(file %s, line %d)\n",
536  __FILE__,
537  __LINE__);
538  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
539 #endif
540  Amat->lambda_max = max_eigen;
541  Amat->lambda_min = -12345.6789;
542  if ( max_eigen <= 0.0 ) {
543  printf("Gen_Prolongator warning : max eigen <= 0.0 \n");
544  max_eigen = 1.0;
545  }
546 
547  break;
548 
549  case ML_USE_POWER: /* use ML's power method */
550  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 5)
551  printf("power method\n");
552  kdata = ML_Krylov_Create( ml->comm );
553  ML_Krylov_Set_PrintFreq( kdata, 0 );
554  ML_Krylov_Set_MaxIterations(kdata, Amat->spectral_radius_max_iters);
555  ML_Krylov_Set_ComputeNonSymEigenvalues( kdata );
556  ML_Krylov_Set_Amatrix(kdata, Amat);
557  ML_Krylov_Solve(kdata, Nfine, NULL, NULL);
558  max_eigen = ML_Krylov_Get_MaxEigenvalue(kdata);
559  Amat->lambda_max = max_eigen;
560  Amat->lambda_min = kdata->ML_eigen_min;
561  ML_Krylov_Destroy( &kdata );
562  if ( max_eigen <= 0.0 ) {
563  printf("Gen_Prolongator warning : max eigen <= 0.0 \n");
564  max_eigen = 1.0;
565  }
566 
567  break;
568 
569  default: /* using matrix max norm */
570  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 5)
571  printf("matrix max norm\n");
572  max_eigen = ML_Operator_MaxNorm(Amat, ML_TRUE);
573  break;
574 
575  } /* switch( Amat->spectral_radius_scheme ) */
576 
577  } else {
578  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 5)
579  printf("Using stashed eigenvalue estimate");
580  } /* if ((max_eigen < -666.) && (max_eigen > -667)) */
581 
582 
583  widget.omega = ag->smoothP_damping_factor / max_eigen;
584  ml->spectral_radius[level] = max_eigen;
585 
586  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 7 < ML_Get_PrintLevel())
587  printf("Gen_Prolongator (level %d) : Max eigenvalue = %2.4e\n",
588  ag->cur_level, max_eigen);
589 
590  }
591  else /* damping fact = 0 ==> no need to compute spectral radius */
592  {
593  ml->spectral_radius[level] = 1.0;
594  widget.omega = 0.0;
595  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 5 < ML_Get_PrintLevel() )
596  printf("\nProlongator/Restriction smoother (level %d) : damping = %2.3e , sweeps = %d\n", level, ag->smoothP_damping_factor, numSmSweeps );
597 
598  } /* if ( ag->smoothP_damping_factor != 0.0 ) */
599 
600  StopTimer(&t1,&eigenTime);
601  StartTimer(&t1);
602 
603  /* Smooth tentative prolongator. */
604  if ( ag->smoothP_damping_factor != 0.0 && numSmSweeps > 0 )
605  {
606  dampingFactors = (double *) ML_allocate( sizeof(double) * numSmSweeps );
607  if (numSmSweeps == 1)
608  dampingFactors[0] = ag->smoothP_damping_factor;
609  else
610  /* Calculate the proper Chebyshev polynomial coefficients. */
611  ML_AGG_Calculate_Smoothing_Factors(numSmSweeps, dampingFactors);
612 
613  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 5 < ML_Get_PrintLevel() ) {
614  printf("\n");
615  for (ii=0; ii<numSmSweeps; ii++)
616  {
617  if (ag->minimizing_energy == -1)
618  {
619  printf("\nProlongator smoother (level %d) : damping factor #%d = %2.4e\nProlongator smoother (level %d) : ( = %2.4e / %2.4e)\nNon-smoothed restriction is used.\n",
620  level, ii+1, dampingFactors[ii]/ max_eigen, level,
621  dampingFactors[ii], max_eigen );
622  }
623  else
624  {
625  printf("Prolongator/Restriction smoother (level %d) : damping factor #%d = %2.4e\nProlongator/Restriction smoother (level %d) : ( = %2.4e / %2.4e)\n",
626  level, ii+1, dampingFactors[ii]/ max_eigen, level,
627  dampingFactors[ii], max_eigen );
628  }
629  if (ml->symmetrize_matrix == ML_TRUE) printf("Smoothing with A + A^T\n");
630  printf("\n");
631  }
632  }
633 
634  /* Create the prolongator smoother operator, I-omega*inv(D)*A. */
635  AGGsmoother = ML_Operator_Create(ml->comm);
636  ML_Operator_Set_Label(AGGsmoother,"Prolongator smoother");
637  widget.drop_tol = ag->drop_tol_for_smoothing;
638  if (ml->symmetrize_matrix == ML_TRUE) widget.Amat = t3;
639  else widget.Amat = &(ml->Amat[level]);
640  widget.aggr_info = ag->aggr_info[level];
641  ML_Operator_Set_ApplyFuncData(AGGsmoother, widget.Amat->invec_leng,
642  widget.Amat->outvec_leng, &widget,
643  widget.Amat->matvec->Nrows, NULL, 0);
644  ML_Operator_Set_Getrow(AGGsmoother,
645  widget.Amat->getrow->Nrows,
646 #ifdef USE_MOREACCURATE
647  ML_AGG_JacobiMoreAccurate_Getrows);
648 #else
649  ML_AGG_JacobiSmoother_Getrows);
650 #endif
651  ML_CommInfoOP_Clone(&(AGGsmoother->getrow->pre_comm),
652  widget.Amat->getrow->pre_comm);
653 
654  tmpmat2 = Pmatrix;
655  for (ii=0; ii < numSmSweeps; ii++)
656  {
657  /* Set the appropriate prolongator smoother damping factor. */
658  widget.omega = dampingFactors[ii] / max_eigen;
659 
660  if (ii < numSmSweeps-1) {
661  tmpmat1 = tmpmat2;
662  tmpmat2 = ML_Operator_Create(Amat->comm);
663  }
664  else {
665  tmpmat1 = tmpmat2;
666  tmpmat2 = &(ml->Pmat[clevel]);
667  }
668 
669  if (ag->block_scaled_SA == 1) {
670  /* Computed the following:
671  * a) turn off the usual 2 mat mult.
672  * b) Ptemp = A*P
673  * c) Ptemp = Dinv*Ptemp;
674  * d) do an ML_Operator_Add() with the original P.
675  */
676  Ptemp = ML_Operator_Create(Amat->comm);
677  ML_2matmult(Amat, tmpmat1, Ptemp, ML_CSR_MATRIX );
678  ML_AGG_DinvP(Ptemp, mls_widget, Amat->num_PDEs, ROW_SCALE_WITH_D);
679 
680  ML_Operator_Add(tmpmat1, Ptemp, tmpmat2, ML_CSR_MATRIX,
681  -dampingFactors[ii] / max_eigen);
682  ML_Operator_Destroy(&Ptemp);
683  }
684  else
685  ML_2matmult(AGGsmoother, tmpmat1, tmpmat2, ML_CSR_MATRIX );
686 
687  /*Free intermediate matrix I-omega*inv(D)*A, as long as it's not Ptent.*/
688  if (tmpmat1 && tmpmat1 != Pmatrix) ML_Operator_Destroy(&tmpmat1);
689 
690  } /* for (ii=0; ii < numSmSweeps; ii++) */
691 
692  ML_Operator_Destroy(&AGGsmoother);
693  ML_free(dampingFactors);
694 
695  if ((ml->symmetrize_matrix == ML_TRUE) || (ag->use_transpose == ML_TRUE) )
696  {
697  if (t3 != NULL) ML_Operator_Destroy(&t3);
698  if (t2 != NULL) ML_Operator_Destroy(&t2);
699  }
700  if (ag->keep_P_tentative == ML_NO)
701  ML_Operator_Destroy(&Pmatrix);
702  else {
703  if (prev_P_tentatives == NULL) {
704  ag->P_tentative = ML_Operator_ArrayCreate(ag->max_levels);
705  prev_P_tentatives = ag->P_tentative;
706  for (jj = 0; jj < ag->max_levels; jj++) prev_P_tentatives[jj] = NULL;
707  }
708  prev_P_tentatives[clevel] = Pmatrix;
709  }
710 
711  } /* if ( ag->smoothP_damping_factor != 0.0 ) */
712  else if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && 5 < ML_Get_PrintLevel() )
713  printf("Gen_Prolongator (level %d) : not smoothing prolongator\n", level);
714  StopTimer(&t1,&smooPTime);
715  if ( ML_Get_PrintLevel() > 9) {
716  char eigmethod[32];
717 # ifdef ML_TIMING
718  if (ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0)
719  printf("Detailed timing for forming smoothed prolongator (level %d)\n", level);
720 # endif
721  ReportTimer(createPtentTime,"Create tentative P (total)",ml->comm);
722  switch( Amat->spectral_radius_scheme ) {
723  case ML_USE_CG:
724  sprintf(eigmethod,"Eigen estimate (cg) ");
725  break;
726  case ML_USE_POWER:
727  sprintf(eigmethod,"Eigen estimate (power) ");
728  break;
729  default:
730  sprintf(eigmethod,"Eigen estimate (max norm) ");
731  break;
732  }
733  ReportTimer(eigenTime, eigmethod,ml->comm);
734  ReportTimer(smooPTime, "Smooth tentative P ",ml->comm);
735 # ifdef ML_TIMING
736  if (ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0)
737  printf("\n");
738 # endif
739  }
740  ML_Operator_Set_1Levels(&(ml->Pmat[clevel]),
741  &(ml->SingleLevel[clevel]), &(ml->SingleLevel[level]));
742 
743  if (widget.near_bdry != NULL) ML_free(widget.near_bdry);
744  if (mls_widget != NULL) ML_Smoother_Destroy_MLS(mls_widget);
745 
746 #ifdef ML_TIMING
747  ml->Pmat[clevel].build_time = GetClock() - t0;
748  ml->timing->total_build_time += ml->Pmat[clevel].build_time;
749 #endif
750  return 0;
751 } /* ML_AGG_Gen_Prolongator() */

906  }

923  diag = row_lengths[0];
924  row_lengths[0]++;
925  }

944  }
945  }

955  row_lengths[0] = N;

957 */

961  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */

965  values[i] *= -widget->omega/diag_val;
966  values[diag] += 1.;
967 #else

973  values[diag] += 1.;
974  }
975 #else
976  for (i = 0; i < row_lengths[0]; i++)

979 #endif
980 #endif
981 
982  return(1);

1189 /* ************************************************************************* */

1193 int ML_AGG_Gen_DDProlongator(ML *ml,int level, int clevel, void *data)
1194 {
1195  int i, j, Nfine, nbytes, newNlevels, nnz, *col_ind;
1196  int k, newClevel, lengc, lengf, ap_ncols, *ap_cols;

1421  /* 2. compute AP = A * tentP */
1422  /* 3. compute P = tentP - alpha * D^{-1} A tentP */

1426  if ( ag->smoothP_damping_factor != 0.0 )
1427 */

1533  }

1535

1539  ML_Destroy(&newml);

1542  i = 1;

1544  if ( ml->comm->ML_mypid == 0 && ag->print_flag < ML_Get_PrintLevel())
1545  printf("Aggregation : building P complete at level %d\n",level);

1550 #ifdef ML_TIMING

1706  while (getrowfunc((ML_Operator *) getrowdata,1,&i,max_row_nnz,col_ind,col_val,&m)== 0)
1707  {
1708  ML_free( col_ind );
1709  ML_free( col_val );
1710  max_row_nnz = max_row_nnz * 2 + 1;
1711  col_ind = (int *) ML_allocate( max_row_nnz * sizeof(int) );
1712  col_val = (double *) ML_allocate( max_row_nnz * sizeof(double) );
1713  }
1714  for (j = 0; j < m; j++) if (col_ind[j] == i) diagonal[i] = col_val[j];
1715  }
1716  ML_free( col_ind );
1717  ML_free( col_val );
1718 
1719  return 1;
1720 }

1748 /* ************************************************************************* */
1749 /* solve local subproblem using smoothed aggregation */
1750 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
1751 
1752 int ML_AGG_Extract_Matrix(ML_Operator *mat, int *ncols, int **cols,
1753  double ***vals)
1754 {
1755  int i, j, nnz, local_nrows, *col_ind, row_size, max_size;
1756  int index, local_ncols, *local_cols;
1757  double *col_val, **local_vals;
1758  int (*getrowfunc)(ML_Operator *,int,int*,int,int*,double*,int*);
1759  void *getrowdata;
1760  ML_GetrowFunc *getrow_obj;
1761 
1762  local_nrows = mat->outvec_leng;
1763  getrow_obj = mat->getrow;
1764  getrowfunc = getrow_obj->func_ptr;
1765  getrowdata = (void *) mat;
1766 
1767  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1768  /* compute number of nonzeros */
1769  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1770 
1771  max_size = 3;
1772  col_ind = (int *) ML_allocate( max_size * sizeof(int) );
1773  col_val = (double *) ML_allocate( max_size * sizeof(double) );
1774  nnz = 0;
1775  for ( i = 0; i < local_nrows; i++ )
1776  {
1777  while (getrowfunc((ML_Operator *) getrowdata,1,&i,max_size,col_ind,col_val,&row_size)==0)
1778  {
1779  ML_free( col_ind );
1780  ML_free( col_val );
1781  max_size = max_size *2 + 1;
1782  col_ind = (int *) ML_allocate( max_size * sizeof(int) );
1783  col_val = (double *) ML_allocate( max_size * sizeof(double) );
1784  }
1785  nnz += row_size;
1786  if ( row_size > max_size ) max_size = row_size;
1787  }
1788  ML_free( col_ind );
1789  ML_free( col_val );
1790 
1791  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1792  /* extract matrix */
1793  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1794 
1795  col_ind = (int *) ML_allocate( nnz * sizeof(int));
1796  col_val = (double *) ML_allocate( nnz * sizeof(double));
1797  nnz = 0;
1798  for ( i = 0; i < local_nrows; i++ )
1799  {
1800  getrowfunc((ML_Operator *) getrowdata,1,&i,max_size,&col_ind[nnz],&col_val[nnz],&row_size);
1801  nnz += row_size;
1802  }
1803 
1804  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1805  /* find number of distinct nonzero columns */
1806  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1807 
1808  ML_az_sort( col_ind, nnz, NULL, NULL );
1809  local_ncols = 0;
1810  for ( i = 1; i < nnz; i++ )
1811  {
1812  if ( col_ind[i] != col_ind[local_ncols] )
1813  col_ind[++local_ncols] = col_ind[i];
1814  }
1815  local_ncols++;
1816  local_cols = (int *) ML_allocate(local_ncols * sizeof(int));
1817  for ( i = 0; i < local_ncols; i++ ) local_cols[i] = col_ind[i];
1818  ML_free( col_ind );
1819  ML_free( col_val );
1820 
1821  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1822  /* fill in the matrix */
1823  /* ----------------------------------------------------------------- */
1824 
1825  local_vals = (double **) ML_allocate(local_ncols * sizeof(double*));
1826  for ( i = 0; i < local_ncols; i++ )
1827  {
1828  local_vals[i] = (double *) ML_allocate(local_nrows * sizeof(double));
1829  for ( j = 0; j < local_nrows; j++ ) local_vals[i][j] = 0.0;
1830  }
1831 
1832  col_ind = (int *) ML_allocate( max_size * sizeof(int));
1833  col_val = (double *) ML_allocate( max_size * sizeof(double));
1834  for ( i = 0; i < local_nrows; i++ )
1835  {
1836  getrowfunc((ML_Operator *) getrowdata,1,&i,max_size,col_ind,col_val,&row_size);
1837  for ( j = 0; j < row_size; j++ )
1838  {
1839  index = ML_sorted_search( col_ind[j], local_ncols, local_cols);
1840  if ( index >= 0 ) local_vals[index][i] = col_val[j];
1841  }
1842  }
1843  ML_free( col_ind );
1844  ML_free( col_val );
1845 
1846  (*ncols) = local_ncols;
1847  (*cols) = local_cols;
1848  (*vals) = local_vals;
1849  return 1;
1850 }

1997 /* ************************************************************************* */
1998 /* Compute the DOFs that are on the boundary and those that are right next */
1999 /* to the boundary. */
2000 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
2001 int ML_AGG_Compute_Near_Bdry(ML_Operator *Amatrix, char *near_bdry)
2002 {
2003  int Nrows, Nghost = 0, allocated = 0, *rowi_col = NULL, rowi_N, count2;
2004  int i, j, bsize, flag;
2005  double *dtemp, *rowi_val = NULL, sum;
2006 
2007 
2008  Nrows = Amatrix->outvec_leng;
2009 
2010  /* ============================================================= */
2011  /* Figure out where the Dirichlet points are on the fine grid. */
2012  /* ============================================================= */
2013 
2014  if (Amatrix->getrow->pre_comm != NULL)
2015  Nghost = Amatrix->getrow->pre_comm->total_rcv_length;
2016 
2017  /* near_bdry = (char *) ML_allocate(sizeof(char)*(Nrows+Nghost+1)); */
2018  dtemp = (double *) ML_allocate(sizeof(double)*(Nrows+Nghost+1));
2019  if (dtemp == NULL) pr_error("ml_agg_MIS: out of space.\n");
2020 
2021  for (i = 0; i < Nrows+Nghost; i++) dtemp[i] = 0.;
2022 
2023  for (i = 0; i < Nrows; i++) {
2024  ML_get_matrix_row(Amatrix, 1, &i, &allocated, &rowi_col, &rowi_val,

2026  count2 = 0;
2027  for (j = 0; j < rowi_N; j++) if (rowi_val[j] != 0.) count2++;

2032

2036  for (j = 0; j < bsize; j++) {
2037  sum += dtemp[i*bsize+j];
2038  }
2039  if (sum != 0.) {
2040  for (j = 0; j < bsize; j++) dtemp[i*bsize+j] = 1.;
2041  }
2042  }
2043 
2044 
2045 
2046  ML_exchange_bdry(dtemp,Amatrix->getrow->pre_comm,Amatrix->outvec_leng,
2047  Amatrix->comm, ML_OVERWRITE,NULL);
2048  for (i = 0; i < Nrows+Nghost; i++) {
2049  if (dtemp[i] == 1.) near_bdry[i] = 'T';
2050  else near_bdry[i] = 'F';
2051  }
2052 
2053  /* Figure out who touches a Dirichlet point */
2054 
2055  for (i = 0; i < Nrows; i++) {
2056  ML_get_matrix_row(Amatrix, 1, &i, &allocated, &rowi_col, &rowi_val,
2057  &rowi_N, 0);

2060  if (count2 != 0) near_bdry[i] = 'T';
2061  }
2062 
2063  for (i = 0; i < Nrows/bsize; i++) {
2064  flag = 0;
2065  for (j = 0; j < bsize; j++) {
2066  if (near_bdry[i*bsize+j] == 'T') flag = 1;
2067  }
2068  if (flag == 1) {
2069  for (j = 0; j < bsize; j++) {
2070  near_bdry[i*bsize+j] = 'T';
2071  }
2072  }
2073  }
2074 
2075 
2076 
2077  ML_free(rowi_col); ML_free(rowi_val);
2078  rowi_col = NULL; rowi_val = NULL;
2079  allocated = 0;
2080 
2081  ML_free(dtemp);
2082 
2083  return 0;
2084 }

2161 /*****************************************************************************/
2162 /* I believe this routine works in the following way. The two dimensional */
2163 /* array Filter has already been computed. Filter[i][0] indicates how many */
2164 /* column entries in the ith row WILL be removed. Filter[i][1:Filter[i][0]] */
2165 /* indicates which column values should be removed. In addition, the matrix */
2166 /* diagonal is also modified so that piecewise constants are still in the */
2167 /* null space (assuming that they were originally). This code appears to work*/
2168 /* even when we have a block PDE system. */
2169 /*****************************************************************************/
2170 
2171 static int ML_Aux_Getrow(ML_Operator *data, int N_requested_rows, int requested_rows[],
2172  int allocated_space, int columns[], double values[],
2173  int row_lengths[])
2174 {
2175 
2176  int ierr;
2177  int i, j, count, mod;
2178  int BlockCol, BlockRow, RowMod;
2179  double DiagValue = 0.0;
2180  int DiagID;
2181  int* Filter;
2182 
2183  ierr = (*(data->aux_data->aux_func_ptr))(data, N_requested_rows, requested_rows,
2184  allocated_space, columns, values, row_lengths);
2185  if (ierr == 0)
2186  return(0);
2187 
2188  if (N_requested_rows != 1) {
2189  fprintf(stderr, "ML_Aux_Getrow() works only if N_requested_rows == 1\n"
2190  "(file %s, line %d)\n",
2191  __FILE__, __LINE__);
2192  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2193  }
2194 
2195  /* new part */
2196  mod = data->invec_leng / data->aux_data->filter_size;
2197  BlockRow = requested_rows[0] / mod;
2198  RowMod = requested_rows[0] % mod;
2199  Filter = data->aux_data->filter[BlockRow];
2200  count = 0;
2201  DiagID = -1;
2202  DiagValue = 0.0;
2203 
2204  for (i = 0 ; i < row_lengths[0] ; ++i)
2205  {
2206  BlockCol = columns[i] / mod;
2207 
2208  if (BlockCol == BlockRow)
2209  {
2210  columns[count] = columns[i];
2211  values[count] = values[i];
2212  if (requested_rows[0] == columns[i]) DiagID = count;
2213  ++count;
2214  goto after;
2215  }
2216 
2217  /* different block col, same equation */
2218  for (j = 0 ; j < Filter[0] ; ++j)
2219  {
2220  /* look for elements to discard */
2221  if (Filter[j + 1] == BlockCol)
2222  {
2223  /* We modify the matrix diagonal so that the constant vector */
2224  /* is still in the null space (assuming that the constant */
2225  /* was in the original matrix null space). For block pde */
2226  /* systems we need to check that both the column and the row */
2227  /* correspond to the same DOF within the node. */
2228  /* Note: This code will not preserve the null space if it is */
2229  /* not given by piecewise constants. */
2230 
2231  if (columns[i] % mod == RowMod) {
2232  DiagValue += values[i];
2233  }
2234  goto after;
2235  }
2236  }
2237  columns[count] = columns[i];
2238  values[count] = values[i];
2239  ++count;
2240 after:
2241  continue;
2242  }
2243 
2244  if (DiagID == -1)
2245  {
2246  fprintf(stderr, "Diagonal not defined for row %d\n", requested_rows[0]);
2247  }
2248 
2249  values[DiagID] += DiagValue;
2250  row_lengths[0] = count;
2251 
2252  /* EXPERIMENTAL: Special handling code for handling zero diagonals.
2253  If sufficient dropping has occurred to zero the diagonal, we reset the
2254  diagonal to its normal value. This keeps the eigenvalue
2255  estimate for prolongator smoothing from being hideously wrong.
2256  */
2257  if(ML_dabs(values[DiagID] / (values[DiagID] - DiagValue)) < 1e-10)
2258  values[DiagID]= -DiagValue;
2259 
2260  return(ierr);
2261 }

2263 #define ML_FUNCTION_NAME "ML_Project_Coordinates"
2264 void ML_Project_Coordinates(ML_Operator* Amat, ML_Operator* Pmat,
2265  ML_Operator* Cmat)

2489 /*
2490  * This function allocates the filter field of the aux_data
2491  * structure. Filter[i] contains the thrown away nonzero
2492  * connections in amalgamated row i. Filter[i][0] is the number
2493  * of removed connections; connection `j' is stored in
2494  * Filter[0][j + 1]
2495  */
2496 static void ML_Init_Aux(ML* ml, int level)
2497 {
2498  int i, j, n, count, num_PDEs, BlockRow, BlockCol;
2499  double threshold;
2500  int* columns;
2501  double* values;
2502  int allocated, entries = 0;
2503  int N_dimensions;
2504  int DiagID;
2505  double DiagValue;
2506  int** filter;
2507  double dist;
2508  double* x_coord,* y_coord,* z_coord;
2509  ML_Aggregate_Viz_Stats *grid_info;
2510  double *LaplacianDiag;
2511  int Nghost;
2512 
2513  ML_Operator* A = &(ml->Amat[level]);
2514  grid_info = (ML_Aggregate_Viz_Stats *) A->to->Grid->Grid;
2515  num_PDEs = A->num_PDEs;
2516  N_dimensions = grid_info->Ndim;
2517  x_coord = grid_info->x;
2518  y_coord = grid_info->y;
2519  z_coord = grid_info->z;
2520  if (x_coord == NULL) {
2521  printf("ML_Init_Aux: Cannot use aux options without supplying coordinates\n");
2522  exit(1);
2523  }
2524 
2525  threshold = A->aux_data->threshold;
2526  ML_Operator_AmalgamateAndDropWeak(A, num_PDEs, 0.0);
2527 
2528  n = A->invec_leng;
2529  Nghost = ML_CommInfoOP_Compute_TotalRcvLength(A->getrow->pre_comm);
2530 
2531  LaplacianDiag = (double *) ML_allocate((A->getrow->Nrows+Nghost+1)*
2532  sizeof(double));
2533 
2534  filter = (int**) ML_allocate(sizeof(int*) * n);
2535 
2536  allocated = 128;
2537  columns = (int *) ML_allocate(allocated * sizeof(int));
2538  values = (double *) ML_allocate(allocated * sizeof(double));
2539 
2540  for (i = 0 ; i < n ; ++i) {
2541  BlockRow = i;
2542  DiagID = -1;
2543  DiagValue = 0.0;
2544 
2545  ML_get_matrix_row(A,1,&i,&allocated,&columns,&values, &entries,0);
2546 
2547  for (j = 0; j < entries; j++) {
2548  BlockCol = columns[j];
2549  if (BlockRow != BlockCol) {
2550  dist = 0.0;
2551  switch (N_dimensions) {
2552  case 3:
2553  dist += (z_coord[BlockRow] - z_coord[BlockCol]) * (z_coord[BlockRow] - z_coord[BlockCol]);
2554  case 2:
2555  dist += (y_coord[BlockRow] - y_coord[BlockCol]) * (y_coord[BlockRow] - y_coord[BlockCol]);
2556  case 1:
2557  dist += (x_coord[BlockRow] - x_coord[BlockCol]) * (x_coord[BlockRow] - x_coord[BlockCol]);
2558  }
2559 
2560  if (dist == 0.0) {
2561  printf("node %d = %e ", i, x_coord[BlockRow]);
2562  if (N_dimensions > 1) printf(" %e ", y_coord[BlockRow]);
2563  if (N_dimensions > 2) printf(" %e ", z_coord[BlockRow]);
2564  printf("\n");
2565  printf("node %d = %e ", j, x_coord[BlockCol]);
2566  if (N_dimensions > 1) printf(" %e ", y_coord[BlockCol]);
2567  if (N_dimensions > 2) printf(" %e ", z_coord[BlockCol]);
2568  printf("\n");
2569  printf("Operator has inlen = %d and outlen = %d\n",
2570  A->invec_leng, A->outvec_leng);
2571  }
2572 
2573  dist = 1.0 / dist;
2574  DiagValue += dist;
2575  }
2576  else if (columns[j] == i) {
2577  DiagID = j;
2578  }
2579  }
2580 
2581  if (DiagID == -1) {
2582  fprintf(stderr, "ERROR: matrix has no diagonal!\n"
2583  "ERROR: (file %s, line %d)\n",
2584  __FILE__, __LINE__);
2585  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2586  }
2587  LaplacianDiag[BlockRow] = DiagValue;
2588  }
2589  if ( A->getrow->pre_comm != NULL )
2590  ML_exchange_bdry(LaplacianDiag,A->getrow->pre_comm,A->getrow->Nrows,
2591  A->comm, ML_OVERWRITE,NULL);
2592 
2593 
2594  for (i = 0 ; i < n ; ++i) {
2595  BlockRow = i;
2596 
2597  ML_get_matrix_row(A,1,&i,&allocated,&columns,&values, &entries,0);
2598 
2599  for (j = 0; j < entries; j++) {
2600  BlockCol = columns[j];
2601  if (BlockRow != BlockCol) {
2602  dist = 0.0;
2603  switch (N_dimensions) {
2604  case 3:
2605  dist += (z_coord[BlockRow] - z_coord[BlockCol]) * (z_coord[BlockRow] - z_coord[BlockCol]);
2606  case 2:
2607  dist += (y_coord[BlockRow] - y_coord[BlockCol]) * (y_coord[BlockRow] - y_coord[BlockCol]);
2608  case 1:
2609  dist += (x_coord[BlockRow] - x_coord[BlockCol]) * (x_coord[BlockRow] - x_coord[BlockCol]);
2610  }
2611 
2612  dist = 1.0 / dist;
2613  values[j] = dist;
2614  }
2615  }
2616 
2617  count = 0;
2618  for (j = 0 ; j < entries ; ++j) {
2619  if ( (i != columns[j]) &&
2620  (values[j]*values[j] <
2621  LaplacianDiag[BlockRow]*LaplacianDiag[columns[j]]*threshold*threshold)){
2622  columns[count++] = columns[j];
2623  }
2624  }
2625 
2626  /* insert the rows */
2627  filter[BlockRow] = (int*) ML_allocate(sizeof(int) * (count + 1));
2628  filter[BlockRow][0] = count;
2629 
2630  for (j = 0 ; j < count ; ++j)
2631  filter[BlockRow][j + 1] = columns[j];
2632 
2633  }
2634 
2635  ML_free(columns);
2636  ML_free(values);
2637 
2638  ML_free(LaplacianDiag);
2639 
2640  ML_Operator_UnAmalgamateAndDropWeak(A, num_PDEs, 0.0);
2641 
2642  A->aux_data->aux_func_ptr = A->getrow->func_ptr;
2643  A->getrow->func_ptr = ML_Aux_Getrow;
2644  A->aux_data->filter = filter;
2645  A->aux_data->filter_size = n;
2646 
2647 }

2774 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
2775 
2776 int ML_Gen_MultiLevelHierarchy(ML *ml, int fine_level,
2777  int (*user_next_level)(ML *, int, void *),
2778  int (*user_gen_restriction)(ML *, int, int, void *),
2779  int (*user_gen_prolongator)(ML *, int, int, void *),
2780  void *user_data)
2781 {
2782  int level, next, flag, count=1;
2783  int i, j, k, bail_flag, N_input_vector;
2784  ML_Operator *Amat, *Pmat, *Ptent;
2785  ML_CommInfoOP *getrow_comm;

2788  ML_Aggregate *ag;
2789  char str[80];
2790  int R_is_Ptranspose;
2791 
2792 #ifdef ML_TIMING
2793  double trap, /*RAP*/
2794  tpart, /*repartitioning: Zoltan, migrating Acoarse, prolongator, restrictor*/
2795  tprol, /*prolongator generation (e.g., agg+QR)*/
2796  trest, /*restriction generation (e.g., agg+QR)*/
2797  tmisc, /*any operations not accounted for elsewhere*/

2799 #endif
2800 
2801  ml->ML_finest_level = fine_level;
2802  level = fine_level;
2803  next = user_next_level(ml, level, user_data);
2804  k = 0;
2805  ml->LevelID[k++] = fine_level;
2806

3373  level,
3374  ag->smoothP_damping_factor,
3375  dtemp2 );
3376  }

3378  /* use old-fashioned functions to create the actual prolongator based on A */

3381 
3382  } else {

3384  /* Added on Jul-05 */
3385  switch (ag->minimizing_energy) {

3387  if (ag->P_tentative == NULL)

3478 /******************************************************************************
3479 Calculate the damping parameters for the case that the tentative prolongator is
3480 smoothed by more than one iteration of damped Jacobi. This corresponds to a
3481 higher degree Chebyshev polynomial in factored form.
3482 ******************************************************************************/
3483 
3484 void ML_AGG_Calculate_Smoothing_Factors(int numSweeps, double *factors)
3485 {
3486  int i;
3487  int deg = 2*numSweeps+1; /* degree of the Chebyshev poly */
3488  double pi=4.e0 * atan(1.e0); /* 3.141592653589793115998e0; */
3489  double root;
3490 
3491  for (i=0; i<numSweeps; i++) {
3492  root = cos( (2*i+1) * pi / (2*deg) );
3493  factors[i] = 1.0 / (root*root);
3494  }
3495 }

3497 /* This function block scales matrices. It can be invoked in differnt ways. */
3498 /* Let X be the matrix to be scaled and D be the block diagonal scaling */
3499 /* matrix. Here are the possibilities: */
3500 /* */
3501 /* a) D X (ROW_SCALE_WITH_D) */
3502 /* Implemented by first transposing, scaling, and transposing */
3503 /* back: ( X^T D^T )^T. This was probably done so things were */
3504 /* contiguous for the scaling. One REAL tricky thing is that */
3505 /* ML_Operator_Transpose() only locally transposes data and then */
3506 /* sets up a strange post communication object. This is IMPORTANT*/
3507 /* because if data is shuffled (e.g. a real transpose), it would */
3508 /* be necessary to communicate D. However, this is not needed as*/
3509 /* all data remains local. The catch is that the second transpose*/
3510 /* has messed up communication as ML_Operator_Transpose() was not*/
3511 /* designed to work with post communication on input. So we */
3512 /* ignore the communication object produced by the transpose and */
3513 /* use X's communication object in the final result. By the way, */
3514 /* ML_Operator_ExplicitDinvA() looks like it has the same */
3515 /* functionality (without all this transpose stuff). Probably, */
3516 /* these functions were written without knowledge of each other. */
3517 /* b) X D^T (COL_SCALE_WITH_DT) */
3518 /* X is not tranposed here. Communication is used on D. */
3519 /* c) D^T X (ROW_SCALE_WITH_DT) */
3520 /* Probably never tested. Should function similar to a) and so */
3521 /* hopefully just works. */
3522 /* d) X D (COL_SCALE_WITH_D) */
3523 /* Probably never tested. Should function similar to b) and so */
3524 /* hopefully just works. */
3525 /* */
3526 /* One nasty issue is that nnz(D X) >= nnz(X). That is, we might have some */
3527 /* new nonzeros. This means that both the data object and the communication */
3528 /* object need to be changed first to accommodate the new nonzeros before any */
3529 /* scaling is applied. */

3958 int FindCpts(int PtsPerLine, int CoarsenRate, int Thin, int **LayerCpts)
3959 {
3960 /*
3961  * Given the number of points in the z direction (PtsPerLine) and a
3962  * coarsening rate (CoarsenRate), determine which z-points will serve
3963  * as Cpts and return the total number of Cpts.
3964  *
3965  * Input
3966  * PtsPerLine: Number of fine level points in the z direction
3967  *
3968  * CoarsenRate: Roughly, number of Cpts = (PtsPerLine+1)/CoarsenRate - 1
3969  *
3970  * Thin: Must be either 0 or 1. Thin decides what to do when
3971  * (PtsPerLine+1)/CoarsenRate is not an integer.
3972  *
3973  * Thin == 0 ==> ceil() the above fraction
3974  * Thin == 1 ==> floor() the above fraction
3975  *
3976  * Output
3977  * LayerCpts Array where LayerCpts[i] indicates that the
3978  * LayerCpts[i]th fine level layer is a Cpt Layer.
3979  * Note: fine level layers are assumed to be numbered starting
3980  * a one.
3981  */
3982  double temp, RestStride, di;
3983  int NCpts, i;
3984  int NCLayers = -1;
3985  int FirstStride;
3986 
3987  temp = ((double) (PtsPerLine+1))/((double) (CoarsenRate)) - 1.0;
3988  if (Thin == 1) NCpts = (int) ceil(temp);
3989  else NCpts = (int) floor(temp);
3990 
3991  if (PtsPerLine == 1) { printf("cannot coarsen further\n"); return -1; }
3992  if (NCpts < 1) NCpts = 1;
3993 
3994 
3995 
3996  FirstStride= (int) ceil( ((double) PtsPerLine+1)/( (double) (NCpts+1)));
3997  RestStride = ((double) (PtsPerLine-FirstStride+1))/((double) NCpts);
3998 
3999  NCLayers = (int) floor((((double) (PtsPerLine-FirstStride+1))/RestStride)+.00001);
4000 
4001  if ( NCLayers != NCpts) { printf("sizes do not match %d %d\n",NCpts,NCLayers); exit(1); }
4002  *LayerCpts = (int *) malloc((NCLayers+1)*sizeof(int));
4003 
4004  di = (double) FirstStride;
4005  for (i = 1; i <= NCpts; i++) {
4006  (*LayerCpts)[i] = (int) floor(di);
4007  di += RestStride;
4008  }
4009 
4010  return(NCLayers);
4011 }

4021 int MakeSemiCoarsenP(int Ntotal, int nz, int CoarsenRate, int LayerId[],

4032 /*
4033  * Given a CSR matrix (OrigARowPtr, OrigAcols, OrigAvals), information
4034  * describing the z-layer and vertical line (LayerId and VertLineId)
4035  * of each matrix block row, a coarsening rate, and dofs/node information,
4036  * construct a prolongator that coarsening to semicoarsening in the z-direction
4037  * using something like an operator-dependent grid transfer. In particular,
4038  * matrix stencils are collapsed to vertical lines. Thus, each vertical line
4039  * gives rise to a block tridiagonal matrix. BlkRows corresponding to
4040  * Cpts are replaced by identity matrices. This tridiagonal is solved
4041  * to determine each interpolation basis functions. Each Blk Rhs corresponds
4042  * to all zeros except at the corresponding C-pt which has an identity
4043  *

4045  * this processor.
4046  *

4048  * start from 1. In most parts of the code, this 1 offset is kept
4049  * (in some cases wasting the first element of the array). The
4050  * input and output matrices of this function has been changed to
4051  * have offsets/rows/columns which start from 0. LayerId[] and
4052  * VertLineId[] currently start from 1.

4054  * Input

4056  * Ntotal Number of fine level Blk Rows owned by this processor
4057  *
4058  * nz Number of vertical layers. Note: partitioning must be done
4059  * so that each processor owns an entire vertical line. This
4060  * means that nz is the global number of layers, which should
4061  * be equal to the local number of layers.
4062  * CoarsenRate Rate of z semicoarsening. Smoothed aggregation-like coarsening
4063  * would correspond to CoarsenRate = 3.

4065  * layer number associated with the dofs within BlkRow.

4067  * vertical line id (from 0 to Ntotal/nz-1) of BlkRow. All
4068  * BlkRows associated with nodes along the same vertical line
4069  * in the mesh should have the same LineId.
4070  * DofsPerNode Number of degrees-of-freedom per mesh node.
4071  *
4072  * OrigARowPtr, CSR arrays corresponding to the fine level matrix.

4074  * OrigAvals
